$ GRUB
abbr: Grand Unified Bootloader
wp:GNU_GRUB

GRUB can not only load Linux but other Operating Systems as well.


Arguably the most flexible →development/boot-loader for →Linux/index. Other Linux boot loader are → Linux/booting/SYSLINUX and → Linux/booting/LILO.

→ Linux/fhs/usr/lib/grub/_cpu_-_platform_/index[image directory] (s.a. → Linux/booting/GRUB/image-files).

{ Installing GRUB

  GRUB is usually installed into the → hardware/harddisk/MBR[MBR}, using → Linux/shell/commands/grub-install[`grub-install`], for example `grub-install → Linux/fhs/dev/sdX[/dev/sda]``.

}

{ Two boot methods

  GRUB boots either
  • the OS directly, or
  • it uses *chain-load* which loads another →Linux/booting/boot-loader.


}

{ Windows

  GRUB cannot directly boot Windows, it needs the *chain-load* mechanism.

}

